    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Stephanie Rosenbloom's article ''Grade-School Girls, Grown-Up Gossip'' (May 27) struck a responsive chord. My husband and I were traveling with our 13-year-old grandson in March. Our grandson was appalled that we were staying at a Hilton, as he thought the profits were going directly to Paris Hilton.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Stephanie Rosenbloom's article ''Grade-School Girls, Grown-Up Gossip'' (May 27) struck a responsive chord. My husband and I were traveling with our 13-year-old grandson in March. Our grandson was appalled that we were staying at a Hilton, as he thought the profits were going directly to Paris Hilton.</p>
        <p>That said, I think it is a tribute to the parents of the children in this article -- and to all the other parents who are doing their jobs -- that they have instilled their children with the values necessary to make such judgments.</p>
        <p>DEBORAH Green  Fair Haven, N.J.</p>
      </block>
